About the project:
- You are building a platform called "BuildIt" with a tagline "Discover. Develop. Disrupt."
-This platform is for people to post their projects with title, description, technologies, demo link, price, and attachments.
-Attachments include doc files, text files, images, videos, or other files, stored in Google Cloud Storage.
-Users can search for projects by entering a keyword in the search bar and hitting enter. It will search for projects by title, description, and technologies.
-Users can download attachments.
-Project owners can delete or edit projects.
-Notifications are sent to the project owner through email and in-app when a project is purchased.
-People can buy projects by clicking on the project and then clicking on the buy button.
-People can pay for projects using Paypal.
-After payment, the project owner will receive an email with the project details and the payment details.
-Payments are held for 7 days in an escrow system built using Stripe to ensure satisfaction for both buyer and seller.
-After 7 days, the payment is released to the project owner.
-Both buyer and seller will receive a satisfaction form after 7 days to confirm if the code has been delivered and is functional.
-Payments are released to the project owner (after dedducting commission of 12%) after both parties confirm satisfaction through the form.
-If there’s a dispute, admins can intervene and decide whether to release or refund the payment.
-Buyers can view the contact information of the project owner (email or social media links) after purchase to communicate directly.
-A deployed link (optional) can be added by the project owner to showcase the live project demo.


Code Implementation Guidelines:
-Use Next.js, React, Tailwind CSS, and Prisma with PostgreSQL.
